   "source": [
    "### 3.3 Normalize and clean weather schema\n",
    "Align weather fields to project format, enforce Jan-May 2020 daily scope, and keep Meteostat Celsius units."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### 3.3.1 Standardize weather column names\n",
    "Normalize known Meteostat column variations so downstream merge logic is consistent."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if \"time\" in weather.columns and \"date\" not in weather.columns:\n",
    "    weather = weather.rename(columns={\"time\": \"date\"})\n",
    "\n",
    "if \"temp\" in weather.columns and \"tavg\" not in weather.columns:\n",
    "    weather = weather.rename(columns={\"temp\": \"tavg\"})\n",
    "\n",
    "if \"datetime\" in weather.columns and \"date\" not in weather.columns:\n",
    "    weather[\"datetime\"] = pd.to_datetime(weather[\"datetime\"], errors=\"coerce\")\n",
    "    weather[\"date\"] = weather[\"datetime\"].dt.floor(\"D\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if \"date\" not in weather.columns and \"time\" in weather.columns:\n",
    "    weather[\"date\"] = pd.to_datetime(weather[\"time\"], errors=\"coerce\").dt.floor(\"D\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### 3.3.2 Normalize daily weather index and numeric schema\n",
    "Build a daily weather table keyed by `date` and convert weather features to numeric."
   ]
